title: Latest Sun Sentinel Golf Results (Nov. 19)
text:
The Boca Raton boys golf team will get another crack to win a Class 3A state championship.
Led by senior Zachary Bariso, the Bobcats earned that right on Monday by winning the Region 7-3A tournament at Jacaranda Golf Club with a score of 307, four strokes better than second place Spanish River (311). Park Vista was third at 320.
Bariso finished with a 1-over par 73 for medalist honors, a shot better than Matthew Galluzzo of St. Thomas Aquinas.
Spanish River also advanced to the state tournament for the first time since 2008 when they finished seventh. Eduardo Blochtein led the Sharks with a 2-over par 74.
Boca Raton returns to the 3A state tournament after finishing a school record second place to Lake Mary last year at Deer Island Country Club in Tavares. Boca, which trailed by a stroke after the first round ended up finished five back after the second day.
Galluzzo and Jordan Reeves of Park Vista, who finished tied for fourth with a 75, each advanced to state as individual qualifiers.
